Value.value: The forest is thick here, and the path barely visible between the roots of the trees. A rich scent of damp soil fills your nostrils, tinged with something sharper. Through the trees you can see the unnatural angles made by human habitation.
Taking a moment to listen to the forest, you hear the usual rustling and creaking of the living Wealdath - and underneath it, a quiet skittering…
You catch tiny glimpses of movement among the leaf-mold. It could be nothing, of course…
